title: Grateful Dead Live at Great Western LA Forum on 1989-12-09
lineage: M-DAT -> DAT/1 -> Tascam DA-30 -> HHb CDR 800 PRO via analog i/o; CDR>EAC>TLH(6)>FLAC
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Mexicali Blues, Cumberland Blues, Bird Song, One More Saturday Night

Set 2

Foolish Heart, Playin' In The Band-> Crazy Fingers-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band, Drums-> Jam-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> Hey Jude Reprise-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

reviews.review_text: I was there This was my first and only Dead show and I have the ticket stub to prove it.  It was everything I had expected it to be.  Great crowd, great venue, great music.  I couldn't have asked for anything more, except a ticket to the next night's show.
